{"lemma":"فِقْهُ","slug":"فِقْهُ","root":"ف.ق.ه","root_slug":"ف-ق-ه","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ق-ه","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34359","n34363","n34364"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%90%D9%82%D9%92%D9%87%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to understand, to comprehend","tags":["intransitive","stative"],"examples":[{"text":"قَالَ رَبِّ ٱشْرَحْ لِي صَدْرِي / وَيَسِّرْ لِي أَمْرِي / وَٱحْلُلْ عُقْدَةً مِّن لِّسَانِي / يَفْقَهُوا قَوْلِي / وَٱجْعَل لِّي وَزِيرًا مِّنْ أَهْلِي / هَارُونَ أَخِي / اُشْدُدْ بِهِ أَزْرِي / وَأَشْرِكْهُ فِي أَمْرِي / كَيْ نُسَبِّحَكَ كَثِيرًا / وَنَذْكُرَكَ كَثِيرًا / إِنَّكَ كُنْتَ بِنَا بَصِيرًا"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be knowledgeable, especially in matters of jurisprudence","tags":["intransitive","stative"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to instruct, to teach, especially in fiqh","tags":["causative","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fiqh, jurisprudence"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"understanding, insight"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَقِهَ (faqiha) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of فَقِهَ (faqiha)."},"ipa":["/fiqh/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34359","headword_ar":"فَقِهَ","root":"fqh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, &c.,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiqohN","text_ar":"فِقْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the verb being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealima","text_ar":"عَلِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the inf. n. like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EilomN","text_ar":"عِلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in measure and in meaning, (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqahN","text_ar":"فَقَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK; [and the same seems to be implied in the Msb and the K;]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faquha","text_ar":"فَقُهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessed, what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiqohN","text_ar":"فِقْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"understanding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and especially"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge of the law"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu Ald~iyni","text_ar":"عِلْمُ الدِّينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (K:) or both are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealima","text_ar":"عَلِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faquha","text_ar":"فَقُهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqaAhapN","text_ar":"فَقَاهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiqohN","text_ar":"فِقْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK,) signifies [peculiarly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessed, knowledge of the law"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilom Al$~ariyEap","text_ar":"عِلْم الشَّرِيعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (S:) or this latter verb signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessed, what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiqopN","text_ar":"فِقْةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a faculty firmly rooted in his mind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) or, accord. to IB,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafaq~aha","text_ar":"تَفَقَّهَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v., as intrans.]: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqiyh","text_ar":"فَقِيه"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v., or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equal to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuqahA='","text_ar":"فُقَها=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elm","text_ar":"علم"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elm","text_ar":"علم"},{"kind":"text","text":".) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN laA yanoqahu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَا يَنْقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one will not understand nor comprehend:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the two verbs are exactly syn.]. (S.) And to the witness one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayofa faqaAhatuka limaA","text_ar":"كَيْفَ فَقَاهَتُكَ لِمَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ohado naAka","text_ar":"اَشْهَدْ نَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How is thy understanding of"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how understandest thou"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what we have made thee to witness?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: it is not said to any other than the witness: (K, TA:) thus in the M: (TA:) or, accord. to Z, it is said to other than the witness. (K, * TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqihahu","text_ar":"فَقِهَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiqohN","text_ar":"فِقْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He understood it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K,) namely, a meaning, (Mgh,) or a thing that one explained to him; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tfq~hhu","text_ar":"تفقّههُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-  See also 3."}],"source_refs":["TA","S","K","Msb","JK","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n34363","headword_ar":"فِقْهٌ","root":"fqh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as a simple subst.] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Understanding"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) of a thing; (Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof; (Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) accord. to IF,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any knowledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing is thus termed: (Msb:) [hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiqohu All~ugapi","text_ar":"فِقْهُ اللُّغَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The science of lexicology"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the title of a work written by him; and of another work, by Eth-Tha'álibee:] and, as used by the lawyers [and others],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfiqohu","text_ar":"الفِقْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"denotes a particular science; (Msb;) it signifies particularly, (S, TA,) or predominantly, (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The science of the law;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jurisprudence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K, TA;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu Al$~ariyEapi","text_ar":"عِلْمُ الشَّرِيعَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu Ald~iyni","text_ar":"عِلْمُ الدِّينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elm Al$ryEp","text_ar":"علم الشريعة"},{"kind":"text","text":",] because of its preëminence (K, TA) above the other kinds of science: (TA:) and more particularly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the science of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuwE","text_ar":"فُرُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"derivative institutes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the law."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n34364","headword_ar":"فَقُهٌ","root":"fqh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; and its fem., with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}